The City of
Johannesburg Emergency Management Services (EMS) on Tuesday treated one person
for smoke inhalation after two rooms in an office building in the central
business district (CBD) were damaged in a fire. EMS
spokesperson Nana Radebe told News24 that firefighters managed to extinguish
the blaze within 40 minutes after an embroidery machine blew up, causing damage
to the building. "An
embroidery machine was short of oil and blew up. Only two rooms were
affected," she said. SOURCE:
NEWS24